data.title: Student Volunteers acknowledged
data.meta_description: The Year 12 students who have volunteered their time over the past year at Ronald McDonald House were acknowledged at the school assembly last week.
data.text:
From Facebook

ANSTO National Science Week Hackathon ü¶â A small group of dedicated Science students took part last week in the ANSTO (Australian Nuclear Science & Technology Organisation) National Science Week Hackathon for 2024. The hackathon was described as a ‚Äòdesign sprint‚Äô with the students given a design brief early on Monday morning and then had three days to look at the problem, design a solution, work out who the end user was and present their solution in video form. The students were challenged to answer the question: ‚ÄòHow might we engage the community in supporting the survival of an endangered species?‚Äô The students were asked to address the brief to their local council who was keen to inspire community engagement and involvement. The hackathon challenged students to think creatively how to engage their local community in helping endangered species whilst also having fun working in teams.

From Facebook

RHYME WITHOUT REASON üòÉ This is the theme for Mercy Day 2024! Created by the SRC Student Leadership Team, the theme encourages students to come together with friends and dress up in imaginative pairings like, ‚Äòpink panther and dancer‚Äô or ‚Äòbarbie and army‚Äô. This captures the essence of our 2024 school theme, ‚ÄòEmbrace, Excel, Empower‚Äô. The concept of a ‚ÄòRhyme Without Reason‚Äô explores the notion that two seemingly unrelated ideas can be united through their rhyme, symbolising what the McAuley community has strived to live out throughout 2024: embracing our differences, excelling in unity, and realising that we are empowered to be stronger together, all guided by the spirit of mercy.
